Recently visited Pasquale's on 4/11/18 for lunch and 4/12/18 for dinner. The restaurant is plain n the inside with a very open atmosphere.Tables scattered about the center of the room with large booths around the  outside edges of the room. he only way I can comment on the food is to say it was outstanding. I had the chicken parm. for lunch. It came with soup or salad. I chose salad. The entre dish had both the chicken and also a healthy serving of ziti as well. The chicken was well cooked but tender juicy and very flavorful . The sauce made the dish. Tons of flavor without being overly spicy. For the dinner meal I chose the Veal Scallopini. This dish had two large veal cutlets well prepared and a large serving of ziti and sauce on the side. The sauce on the veal had mushrooms, green and red pepper strips as well as onions. It was a symphony  of flavor without any one item being dominant which made it excellent. Would go back without hesitation.
